# SoulStep – Web app (apps/soulstep-customer-web)
# Copy to .env and set values. Do not commit .env.
# In production (GCP/Firebase), these are set as GitHub Actions secrets — see PRODUCTION.md Step 5b.

# ── API ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Optional. Backend API base URL.
# When unset, the app uses relative URLs (/api/v1/...) and the Vite dev proxy
# forwards requests to VITE_PROXY_TARGET. Set for production or a non-default port.
# Use 127.0.0.1 (not localhost) on macOS to avoid IPv6 issues.
# VITE_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:3000
# Production:
# VITE_API_URL=https://soulstep-api-834941457147.europe-west1.run.app

# Optional. Proxy target for /api in dev (default: http://127.0.0.1:3000).
# Only used by the Vite dev server — has no effect in production builds.
# VITE_PROXY_TARGET=http://127.0.0.1:3000

# ── Ads ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Optional. Google AdSense publisher ID.
# When unset, ads are disabled on the client side regardless of backend config.
# Get this from your AdSense account: Ads → Overview → Publisher ID.
# VITE_ADSENSE_PUBLISHER_ID=ca-pub-7902951158656200

# ── Error Tracking ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Optional. GlitchTip (Sentry-compatible) DSN for client-side error tracking.
# When unset, error tracking is disabled. Get your DSN from your GlitchTip project settings.
# VITE_GLITCHTIP_DSN=https://<key>@app.glitchtip.com/<project>

# ── Analytics (Umami Cloud) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Optional. Umami Cloud website ID for privacy-friendly analytics.
# Sign up at https://umami.is → free plan → Add website → copy Website ID.
# The script is proxied via /umami to bypass adblockers (same-origin).
# When unset, Umami analytics are disabled.
# VITE_UMAMI_WEBSITE_ID=xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx
